post_text:
In partnership with Save the Children, the Education Service Center, Region 2 is excited to announce their Summer Reading Challenge July 27th through the August 31st!

How to Participate:
· Read a minimum of two books per week.
· Families in Region 2 with children ages 0 to 12th grade are eligible!
· Complete a reading log for each child each week during the challenge using the flyer QR Code or link below. If it is a chapter book, log the chapter number and title. Each chapter is considered one book.
· Each log submitted enters a family into the prize drawing. Prize drawing is a family fun pack with games, books and more!
· Read more than two books? Just submit another reading log! The reading log form requires two books to complete submission.Reading Log Link/Google Form:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdLGY5y70p6mOJm0kt9jsclhDeYzO5dIYN0iqlX7lH6540Hvg/viewform?usp=sf_link

It is time for students new to Calallen ISD to register for the 2020-2021 school year!

Dates: July 29th and 30th

Locations: Campus of Enrollment

New students must complete this process to be enrolled in Calallen ISD for the 2020-2021 school year. For more information regarding procedures and health protocols, visit the Calallen ISD New Student Registration Page.

post_text:
Summer School Reminder:
Calallen ISD will be hosting summer school July 7-23, 2020 for students who are required to attend due to failure. Students must be registered online at https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/QRTZ9MY no later than July 2nd.

For students who need to make up hours in order to earn credit, but passed all classes, families will be contacted regarding the method of delivery for each student. Students requiring make up hours will not report to the summer school campus on July 7th, and are not required to register online.

All campuses are currently closed, causing phone message delivery to be delayed.

ATTENTION CLASS OF 2020 PARENTS

A video is being created for CHS Class of 2020 GRADUATION CEREMONY. If you would like for your senior to be included in the CHS Class of 2020 video, please email 2 pictures. We would like a picture of your child when they were in K-1 and a current picture (preferably a senior portrait). Please email pictures to rsendejo@calallen.org by Tuesday May 19, 2020. THIS VIDEO WILL BE PLAYING DURING THE CEREMONY.

In the email subject line, please type CLASS OF 2020 PICS.
In the message, please include the following statement. "By the delivery of this email I allow this information to be publicly released to recognize my senior."
Please include the seniors full name.
Please include your senior's shirt size.

post_text: Calallen ISD will continue to provide essential meal services to children ages 0-18 for the foreseeable future. We will continue food services in accordance with Nueces County Judge Canales’ Order to Stay at Home which states, “Schools and other entities that typically provide free services to students or member of the public on a pick-up and take-away basis only” may continue to operate. Calallen ISD believes that providing meals to children in our community is a priority during these trying times. Visiting the campus regularly provides a sense of continuity and connection.

Practice social distancing by putting space between yourself and others. Continue to practice healthy habits to help slow the spread of COVID-19.

• Wash your hands for at least 20 seconds
• Clean and then disinfect frequently used surfaces
• Stay home if you’re sick
• Avoid touching your face

November 16, 2019 at 4:36 AM ·

History was made tonight. Coach Phil Danaher claimed his 400th win at Calallen making him the only coach in Texas Football history to win 400 games at one school. And he couldn’t have done it without Steve Campbell and our fabulous coaches and players over the years.

Edcouch Elsa 0

For Friday's game at Port Lavaca, visitor parking is located a good distance away from the stadium. There MIGHT be buses to move people from parking to the stadium. post_text: It was a pleasure to hear the keynote speaker at the State of the District luncheon. Major Casey Doran graduated from #CalallenHS in 1998. Among his many accomplishments, Major Doran is currently serving as an Operational Test Director for the VH-92A Presidential Helicopter Replacement Program, while also flying the In-Service VH-3D and VH-60N helicopters for Presidential Support Missions. The #CalallenHS Manufacturing class presented him with this magnificent plaque! ❤️We are #CalallenProud! #WeAreCalallen 🐾

shared_text:
1440 KEYS with Deanna Stuart: Allstate Insurance.
Paid Partnership ·

Our Student Athlete of the Week presentation took us to Calallen High School today to recognize SR Alyssa Rodriguez. Alyssa has a 5.0 GPA (that's not a mistake), which ranks her in the Top 10% of her senior class. She hopes to sign a NLI to play Volleyball in College next month. In her free time she volunteers at Nursing Homes and has worked the past two summers at the Texas State Aquarium. Keep on making us proud Alyssa!
The Student Athlete of the Week is presented by Deanna Stuart: Allstate Insurance Agency.

post_text:
Congratulations to the members of the Calallen High School Band on their excellent performance at the Beeville Marching Band Contest this past Saturday.
At the Contest, the Calallen Band was Awarded:

1st Place Class 5A Drum Majors
1st Place Class 5A Colorguard
1st Place Class 5A Percussion
1st Class 5A Band
And…
Calallen High School was the Grand Champion Band out of the 30 bands at the contest!

post_text:
‼️ATTENTION SENIORS‼️
All Seniors who haven’t already taken their senior pictures for the Calallen High School yearbook should visit the school auditorium on Monday, Sept. 30 before 3 p.m. through elective classes to take their portraits. There is no fee for this picture. Seniors, whether they take their pictures with the photographer at school on Monday or with one of their choice, must be in school dress code. Dress nice and smile! Senior yearbook pictures are due Oct. 11, emailed by the photographer to calallenwildcatter@gmail.com.

post_text: One of our students won a state-wide contest in her grade level for Don’t’ Mess With Texas! Keep Texas Beautiful and The Texas Department of Transportation have selected artwork by 14 Texan students to appear in the 2020 Don’t mess with Texas® Calendar. The calendar will include 14 winning designs submitted by students from across the state in the annual Don’t mess with Texas K-12 Art Contest. Among these winners is AUBREY THOMAS from Magee Elementary School taught by Mrs. Wimberly Rose. We are #CalallenProud! #WeAreCalallen 🐾👏

post_text: #CalallenMS participated in the Communities in Schools Do the Write Thing Essay Challenge. Two #CalallenMS students were selected for their essays on “Ending Violence Among Young People”. Alayna Sayles and Jared Chase were selected for their essays out of 1,900 essays around the region.👏👏 There were only two overall winners, a male and female, to win an all expense trip to Washington DC! Congrats to Jared Chase who won as overall male for the region! 👊We are #CalallenProud! #WeAreCalallen 🐾⭐️🔖✒️

post_text: Great things are happening around Calallen ISD! Through hard work and vision from various individuals, the groundbreaking ceremony for Calallen West Elementary School took place this afternoon.
text: Great things are happening around Calallen ISD! Through hard work and vision from various individuals, the groundbreaking ceremony for Calallen West Elementary School took place this afternoon.

shared_text:
Calallen Independent School District added 22 new photos — at Calallen Independent School District.
May 13, 2019 · Corpus Christi, TX ·

Calallen ISD with the help of its Board of Trustees and key Bond Committee Members broke ground for Calallen West Elementary. The new elementary will be located off CR69/Hazel Bazemore Road and will house 650 students. It is expected that it will take 14-16 months for the building to be completed. The architect on the project is RWS Architects – Malcolm Gaus; Polasek Construction is the Construction Manager for this project.
